	<string name="splash_payoff_line">Light-Weight Twitter, pump.io and StatusNet Client for Android™</string>
	<string name="user_manual_page_1"><h1><b>AndStatus User Guide</b></h1>\n\n
        <h2><b>1. Getting started</b></h2>\n\n
        Tap \"Get Started\" button below: screen to add new account will be opened.\n
        You may change default Microblogging system (\"Twitter\") to some other 
        (pump.io and StatusNet, in addition to Twitter, are preconfiigured).\n
        For Twitter you are allowed to press \"Add this account\" immediately. 
        For other systems you will be prompted to type your Username and Password before
        the \"Add this account\" gets enabled.\n
        After successful creation of the account please tap \"left arrow\" on an 
        \"Action Bar\" or \"Back\" button on your device. 
        This time Home time line will be opened and will start to load...\n 
        Congratulations! Read below what you can do further.\n\n
        And don\'t forget to add AndStatus widget to the Home screen: 
        the widget will inform you about new messages and may be used to launch AndStatus.\n\n
        <h2><b>2. AndStatus BASICS</b></h2>\n\n
        The first view of AndStatus contains the Home timeline.\n
        In order to perform an action on a message in the list you should <b>hold down</b>
        on it to get a context menu.\n
        You may <b>click</b> on a message to get more details on it or to see
        a conversation tree to which the message belongs.\n
        Tap the <b>Home</b> button on the \"Action bar\" to switch to the other views.\n\n
        <h2><b>3. SENDING AND REPLYING</b></h2>\n\n
        In order to update your status, tap the \"Blog\" button (\"Tweet\" for Twitter),
        type in a text into the text area at the bottom of the screen and tap <b>Send</b>.\n
        In order to reply, <b>hold down</b> a message and select <b>Reply</b>,
        type in your reply at the bottom.\n
        To abort a reply, simply tap the \"Hide\" button to hide the text area.
	</string>
    <string name="user_manual_page_2">
        <h2><b>4. DIRECT MESSAGES</b></h2>\n\n
        Tap the <b>Home</b> (Timeline type) button 
        and select <b>Direct Messages</b> from the list.\n
        In order to <b>delete</b> your direct message (or your public message), 
        <b>hold down</b> on it and select <b>Delete</b>.\n\n
        New messages are fetched to timelines if you have turned on <b>Automatic sync</b>
        in Android Account and Sync settings for this Account. 
        In any case you may always get updates from the Internet
        manually using \"Reload\" command in the Options Menu.\n\n
        <h2><b>5. MENTIONS</b></h2>\n\n
        Tap <b>Home</b> and then select <b>Mentions</b>.\n
        Mentions will list every message that mentions your <b>@username</b>
        (or even mentions of all your AndStatus accounts for a \"combined\" timeline).\n\n
        <h2><b>6. SEARCHING</b></h2>\n\n
        Click \"Menu\" to open the Options Menu and then <b>Search</b> 
        or you can click the <b>Search</b> button on your device.\n
        If you wish to show messages from a specific user, search for \"username\".\n
        To see mentions of a specific user, search for \"@username\".\n
        A search will find any text contained within a message. This simple search
        searches among messages already loaded from the Internet 
        (Global Search is in works now...)\n\n
        Please note that you may request messages from the Internet by any user 
        (an Author or a Sender of the message) selecting 
        \"Messages by UserName\" from the context menu of the message. This is also a sort of Global Search
        which is already implemented. 
    </string>
